00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.840
What Can I Include in Square Footage?

00:00:02.725 --> 00:00:06.365
In this video, we are going to cover
what can and cannot be included when

00:00:06.365 --> 00:00:08.134
listing the square footage of your home.

00:00:09.594 --> 00:00:13.714
Square footage is an important detail
for buyers, but it is also an area

00:00:13.714 --> 00:00:16.815
where mistakes or misunderstandings
can cause problems later.

00:00:17.725 --> 00:00:20.585
The goal is to be accurate,
transparent, and clear.

00:00:21.212 --> 00:00:22.632
Always Disclose Your Source.

00:00:23.275 --> 00:00:26.824
If you list the square footage of
your property, you should always

00:00:26.824 --> 00:00:28.684
disclose where that number came from.

00:00:29.195 --> 00:00:33.735
This might be a prior appraisal,
tax records, a survey, builder

00:00:33.735 --> 00:00:35.214
plans, or another source.

00:00:35.725 --> 00:00:39.755
If you have any reason to believe the
square footage from your source may not

00:00:39.784 --> 00:00:42.424
be accurate, that should be disclosed.

00:00:43.187 --> 00:00:45.187
What Is Typically Included in Texas?

00:00:45.937 --> 00:00:50.707
In Texas, square footage generally
includes interior living areas that

00:00:50.707 --> 00:00:54.317
are finished, enclosed, and part
of the main structure of the home.

00:00:55.025 --> 00:00:58.644
This means bedrooms, bathrooms,
living areas, and other spaces

00:00:58.644 --> 00:00:59.914
that are heated and cooled.

00:01:00.987 --> 00:01:04.987
Interior closets, entryways, utility
rooms, and mud rooms are typically

00:01:04.987 --> 00:01:08.317
included as long as they are finished
and part of the living space.

00:01:10.037 --> 00:01:14.937
Enclosed patios may be included only if
they are heated and cooled and similar

00:01:14.937 --> 00:01:16.487
in quality to the rest of the home.

00:01:17.524 --> 00:01:22.764
Finished attic space may be included if
it conforms to the original structure, is

00:01:22.764 --> 00:01:27.014
heated and cooled, and is finished to the
same standard as the rest of the home.

00:01:27.675 --> 00:01:28.724
What Is Not Included?

00:01:29.487 --> 00:01:32.847
Garages are not included unless they
have been properly converted to living

00:01:32.847 --> 00:01:34.477
space that is heated and cooled.

00:01:34.937 --> 00:01:39.877
Screened patios, unfinished areas,
and open second-floor spaces, such

00:01:39.877 --> 00:01:43.627
as areas above vaulted rooms or
stairways, are also not included.

00:01:45.242 --> 00:01:49.472
Detached spaces, like an office or
guest room in a separate building, are

00:01:49.472 --> 00:01:53.052
measured separately and should not be
combined with the home’s square footage.

00:01:55.054 --> 00:01:58.765
Accurate square footage avoids
misunderstandings and helps keep the sale

00:01:58.765 --> 00:02:01.465
moving forward without unnecessary issues.

